+### 7.8 `Idea.intended_executor` group-target staleness
+
+§7.4 covered the worker-deregistered case. The group-target case
+is parallel: `idea.intended_executor = {"kind": "group", "id":
+"team-x"}`, then `delete_group("team-x")` (or
+`remove_from_group(W, "team-x")` for the only member W) before
+the orchestrator's execution-dispatch decision runs.
+
+**Contract.** The 12a-2 §7.10 rule applies unchanged:
+target eligibility is resolved at claim time, not at assignment
+time. The orchestrator's auto-dispatch copies
+`idea.intended_executor` to `task.target` even if the group is
+empty or deleted. The resulting task stays in `pending` until
+either (a) a worker becomes a member of `team-x` again, or (b) an
+operator runs `reassign_task` (12a-2 §3.6) to point the task at
+a valid target.
+
+**Test (in `test_intended_executor.py::test_group_target_emptied_post_idea_creation`):**
+
+- Create an idea with `intended_executor={"kind": "group", "id":
+  "team-x"}`. Worker W is in team-x.
+- Run the auto-dispatch flow: the resulting execution task has
+  `target={"kind": "group", "id": "team-x"}`.
+- Run `remove_from_group(W, "team-x")`. team-x is now empty.
+- Assert: claim attempts by any worker (including W) fail (W is
+  no longer a team-x member; no other worker is). Task stays
+  pending.
+- Run `reassign_task(task_id, new_target={"kind": "worker", "id":
+  "W"})`. Assert: W can now claim.
+
+**Test (in `test_intended_executor.py::test_group_target_deleted_post_idea_creation`):**
+
+- Same setup, but operator runs `delete_group("team-x")` instead
+  of `remove_from_group`.
+- Assert: claim attempts by any worker fail (the group's
+  membership lookup is empty / not-found).
+- Assert: `reassign_task` to a valid target restores
+  claimability.
+
+The reuse of 12a-2 §7.10 is intentional: 12a-3 doesn't add new
+target-eligibility semantics; `intended_executor` is just an
+ideator-supplied seed for the auto-dispatch's `target` parameter.
